The Roman Catholic Diocese of Blumenau () is a diocese located in the city of Blumenau in the Ecclesiastical province of Florian&lt;U+00F3&gt;polis in Brazil.
History
April 19, 2000: Established as Diocese of Blumenau from the Metropolitan Archdiocese of Florian&lt;U+00F3&gt;polis, Diocese of Joinville and Diocese of Rio do Sul
Leadership
Bishops of Blumenau (Roman rite)
Bishop Ang&lt;U+00E9&gt;lico S&lt;U+00E2&gt;ndalo Bernardino (April 19, 2000 &lt;U+2013&gt; present)
